Police will use maximum force to stop railway vandals, Makueni county commissioner Mohammed Maalim (pictured) has warned. He spoke on Thursday at Mtito Andei standard gauge railway station after meeting security officers. “We want to warn everyone against railway vandalism. Steal at your own peril,” he told reporters at Mtito Andei SGR station. Last month, one person was gunned down at along the railway SGR at Emali. Nzaui police boss Patrick Olwenyi said the man was among three others caught by police officers . He was trying to vandalise guardrails of the new SRG at near Emali town. Maalim said there will be enhanced day and night surveillance to ensure safety of property and passengers using the SGR. Maalim said national government officers will be held accountable for any illegal activities along the SGR line.